Text: Four seasons in a day, and here comes another geopolitical storm!
The EU’s still sulking over the budget like a jealous ex, and France is crying into his croissant about stability—oh, darling, get a grip!
Scotland popped in with cheeky quips about independence, which made me roll my eyes.
Meanwhile, America’s whining about his coffee trade woes.
Sadly, no spotted dick to satisfy everyone’s appetites.
I offered my rose garden as a peace offering, but they’re all too caught up in their bickering.
Alas, more reason to over-apologize, I suppose.
